    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1894-10-29T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1894-10-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="758"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d758">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Gresham</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Terrell</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Department of State</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1894-10-29">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 29, 1894</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your No. 320<note n="1" xml:id="d758fn1">Not printed.</note> received. Your
                    untenable demand that native teachers in American schools be not arrested
                    without your consent may have been due to misapprehension of my telegram of 3d
                    instant. While you will protest against capricious or unreasonable arrest of
                    such persons as occasion requires you will not insist the Government of the
                    Porte shall agree in advance that it will not arrest its own subjects for
                    violating its own laws without your consent.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
